> The xfconf bug got fixed upstream.

@creiter It doesn't seem like they "fixed" it to me, nor does it seem like it's a bug in `xfconf`. They just disabled their (optional) gsettings backend by default (as a workaround), in order to fix their build whilst waiting on upstream fixes.

Closing this issue without reading or addressing the Xfce perspective pretty much guarantees it won't progress or get a proper fix, since both sides seem convinced that it's an "upstream" bug.

